Manchester United could be without midfielder, Paul Pogba due to injury when they tackle AZ Alkmaar in the Europa League on Thursday and Newcastle United in the Premier League on Sunday. According to ESPN, the France World Cup winner aggravate an ankle problem in Man United’s Premier League 1-1 draw against Arsenal on Monday night. The newspaper reports that Pogba complained to Man United manager, Ole Gunner Solskjaer of ankle pain after the match at Old Trafford. Pogba, however, played 90 minutes of the encounter as Arsenal went behind to a Scott McTominay effort, before Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang equalized for Unai Emery’s men as both sides got a point each. The result leaves Man United in tenth position on the Premier League table, with nine points from seven matches. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.